<div class="row">
    <div class="small-12 columns small-centered text-center" id="header" >
        <h1>AUO Schedule</h1>
    </div> 
</div>

<div class="panel" id="intro" >
    <p>
        AUO meets on Sunday nights from 7:30pm to 10:00pm in the UC Conan room, with sectionals or
        social events often happening at 6:30pm. You can download the 2013-2014 "syllabus" with our
        complete schedule and other resources <a href="/files/syllabus1314.pdf">here</a>.
    </p>
</div>
<div class="panel" >
    <p>
    AUO's Spring 2014 Full Concert will be <em> Sunday, April 6 </em> at
    <em>6pm</em> in <em>
        <a href=
            "https://www.google.com/maps/place/5738+Forbes+Ave/@40.4377009,-79.923946,17z/data=!3m1!4b1!4m2!3m1!1s0x8834f201e27087e1:0x21f3ebf9191327df"
            >
            The Jewish Community Center of Greater Pittsburgh
        </a>'s Katz Auditorium
    </em>.  As always, AUO
    Concerts are free and open to the public, and no ticket is required.
    </p>
    <p>
      The All University Orchestra of Carnegie Mellon University is proud to present
      their annual spring concert on April 6th at 6:00 p.m. in the Katz Theatre of
      the Jewish Community Center in Squirrel Hill. Under the direction of Jeffrey
      Klefstad and assisted by Joel Goodloe, the program revolves around “Music
      for a New Age”. Come hear the exuberance of Gioachino Rossini’s Overture to
      La Gazza Ladra, the colorful and edgy instrumental palettes of Samuel
      Barber’s [First] Essay for Orchestra, and the celebration of a national
      identity in Jean Sibelius’ Symphony No. 2. The concert is free and open to
      the public. 
    </p>
    <p>
        <center>
        <a href="/files/poster-spring-2014.jpg">
            <img src="/files/poster-spring-2014.jpg" />
        </a>
        </center>
    </p>
</div>
<div class="panel" >
    <p>
    AUO's Spring 2014 Chamber Concert will be <em> Sunday, April 6 </em> at
    <em>12:30pm</em> in <em>
        <a href=
          "https://www.google.com/maps/place/College+of+Fine+Arts/@40.4418705,-79.9432776,18z/data=!4m2!3m1!1s0x8834f2203442072b:0x98841051c8166489"
            >
            College of Fine Arts
        </a>'s Alumni Concert Hall (ACH)
    </em>.  As always, AUO
    Concerts are free and open to the public, and no ticket is required.
    </p>
    <p>
      The All University Orchestra of Carnegie Mellon University presents a
      Chamber Music concert featuring String Theory, the AUO Flute Choir, and
      Percussion Ensembles on April 27th at 12:30 p.m. held in the Alumni Concert
      Hall in the College of Fine Arts Building. The ensembles will present a
      diverse program of compositions by Hindemith, Holst, Beck, Chavez, and
      Janacek under the direction of Jeffrey Klefstad and assisted by Joel
      Goodloe. The concert is free and open to the public.
    </p>
    <p>
        <center>
        <a href="/files/poster-chamber-spring-2014.pdf">
